README.md
     8‚Üí# Overview
     9‚Üí
    10‚Üí`once_cell` provides two new cell-like types, `unsync::OnceCell` and `sync::OnceCell`. `OnceCell`
    11‚Üímight store arbitrary non-`Copy` types, can be assigned to at most once and provide direct access
    12‚Üíto the stored contents. In a nutshell, API looks *roughly* like this:
    13‚Üí
    14‚Üí```rust
    15‚Üíimpl OnceCell<T> {
    16‚Üí    fn new() -> OnceCell<T> { ... }
    17‚Üí    fn set(&self, value: T) -> Result<(), T> { ... }
    18‚Üí    fn get(&self) -> Option<&T> { ... }
    19‚Üí}
    20‚Üí```
    21‚Üí
    22‚ÜíNote that, like with `RefCell` and `Mutex`, the `set` method requires only a shared reference.
    23‚ÜíBecause of the single assignment restriction `get` can return an `&T` instead of `Ref<T>`
    24‚Üíor `MutexGuard<T>`.
    25‚Üí
    26‚Üí`once_cell` also has a `Lazy<T>` type, build on top of `OnceCell` which provides the same API as
    27‚Üíthe `lazy_static!` macro, but without using any macros:
    28‚Üí
    29‚Üí```rust
    30‚Üíuse std::{sync::Mutex, collections::HashMap};
    31‚Üíuse once_cell::sync::Lazy;
    32‚Üí
    33‚Üístatic GLOBAL_DATA: Lazy<Mutex<HashMap<i32, String>>> = Lazy::new(|| {
    34‚Üí    let mut m = HashMap::new();
    35‚Üí    m.insert(13, "Spica".to_string());
    36‚Üí    m.insert(74, "Hoyten".to_string());
    37‚Üí    Mutex::new(m)
    38‚Üí});
    39‚Üí
    40‚Üífn main() {
    41‚Üí    println!("{:?}", GLOBAL_DATA.lock().unwrap());
    42‚Üí}
    43‚Üí```
    44‚Üí
    45‚ÜíMore patterns and use-cases are in the [docs](https://docs.rs/once_cell/)!
    46‚Üí
    47‚Üí# Related crates
    48‚Üí
    49‚Üí* [double-checked-cell](https://github.com/niklasf/double-checked-cell)
    50‚Üí* [lazy-init](https://crates.io/crates/lazy-init)
    51‚Üí* [lazycell](https://crates.io/crates/lazycell)
    52‚Üí* [mitochondria](https://crates.io/crates/mitochondria)
    53‚Üí* [lazy_static](https://crates.io/crates/lazy_static)
    54‚Üí* [async_once_cell](https://crates.io/crates/async_once_cell)
    55‚Üí* [generic_once_cell](https://crates.io/crates/generic_once_cell) (bring your own mutex)
    56‚Üí
    57‚ÜíParts of `once_cell` API are included into `std` [as of Rust 1.70.0](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/105587).
